        "id": 2,
        "options": {
          "content": "# Zero-Day Demo Dashboard\n\n**Purpose**: Monitor normal vs attack traffic using live metrics.\n\n**How to use**:\n1. Run normal demo in terminal: `USE_KAFKA=false EVENTS_FILE=/home/wini/zero-day/events.jsonl bash scripts/demo_normal.sh`\n2. Watch the **Events/sec** panel increase\n3. Run attack demo: `bash scripts/demo_attack.sh`\n4. Watch **Active Alerts** and **Attack Score** spike\n\n**Panels**:\n- **Stats** (top): Events/sec, Active Alerts, Attack Score\n- **Event Volume**: Incoming event rate (green=<100/s, amber=100-500/s, red=>500/s)\n- **Attack Alerts**: Detected attacks per 5-min window (green=0, amber=1-5, red=>5)\n- **Processing Latency**: p95 milliseconds (green=<200ms, amber=200-500ms, red=>500ms)\n- **Attack Score**: Real-time anomaly/attack score 0-100 (green=<40, amber=40-70, red=>70)\n\n**Metrics from**: Prometheus scraping `localhost:8000/metrics` (demo metrics exporter)",
          "mode": "markdown"
        },
        "pluginVersion": "8.0.0",
        "targets": [],
        "title": "Demo Instructions & Overview",
        "type": "text"
      },
